      Can I try the Adobe Substance 3D apps before purchasing them?
    <span class="accordion-icon"></span></button></div><div aria-labelledby="accordion-1-trigger-1" id="accordion-1-content-1" hidden="true" class="descr-details"><div>Yes. You can start a 30 day free trial and download any Substance 3D app during the trial period. <a href="/products/substance3d/free-trial-download/" daa-ll="Start your free tria-2--Can I try the Adobe ">Start your free trial.</a></div></div><div role="heading" aria-level="3" class="descr-term"><button type="button" id="accordion-1-trigger-2" class="accordion-trigger tracking-header" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion-1-content-2" daa-ll="open-2--What applications ar">
      What applications are included in Adobe Substance 3D plans?
    <span class="accordion-icon"></span></button></div><div aria-labelledby="accordion-1-trigger-2" id="accordion-1-content-2" hidden="true" class="descr-details"><div>The Substance 3D Collection plan includes Painter, Sampler, Designer, Stager, and access to the entire 3D Asset library. The Substance 3D Texturing plan includes Painter, Sampler, Designer, and access to the entire 3D Asset library. <a href="/products/substance3d/plans/" daa-ll="Compare plans here-4--What applications ar">Compare plans here.</a></div></div><div role="heading" aria-level="3" class="descr-term"><button type="button" id="accordion-1-trigger-3" class="accordion-trigger tracking-header" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion-1-content-3" daa-ll="open-3--Are Substance 3D app">
      Are Substance 3D applications included as part of Creative Cloud?
    <span class="accordion-icon"></span></button></div><div aria-labelledby="accordion-1-trigger-3" id="accordion-1-content-3" hidden="true" class="descr-details"><div>No. Substance 3D apps are sold exclusively in the Substance 3D plans. Substance 3D applications are designed to work seamlessly with other Creative Cloud apps, like Photoshop, Illustrator, and After Effects.</div></div><div role="heading" aria-level="3" class="descr-term"><button type="button" id="accordion-1-trigger-4" class="accordion-trigger tracking-header" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion-1-content-4" daa-ll="open-4--What file formats do">
      What file formats do Substance 3D apps support? Can I use Substance 3D materials in other software?
    <span class="accordion-icon"></span></button></div><div aria-labelledby="accordion-1-trigger-4" id="accordion-1-content-4" hidden="true" class="descr-details"><div>Substance 3D supports industry-standard formats and integrates with major DCC tools. Substance materials are cross-platform and integrate seamlessly with most 3D software and rendering engines through standard material formats.</div></div><div role="heading" aria-level="3" class="descr-term"><button type="button" id="accordion-1-trigger-5" class="accordion-trigger tracking-header" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="accordion-1-content-5" daa-ll="open-5--How can Adobe Substa">
